FeedPackage.Title: NetIRC

FeedPackage.Description:
NetIRC2 is an easy-to-use .NET IRC client library. It supports all major features relevant to making a chat client or bot.
NetIRC2 has full support for synchronization contexts. You can use it from a Windows Forms or WPF GUI thread and chat events will be automatically dispatched, allowing you to completely ignore multithreading. It uses byte arrays internally so mixed encodings can be handled. The IrcClient class can even be used as a component in the Forms Designer.
Because it speeds up connect times with some IRC servers, an Ident server is included as well.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: 1.0.0.0 (May 2, 2013): Initial version of NetIRC2. This is a substantially redone version of my original NetIRC library. If you need sample code, I've ported the Chatter client I wrote ages ago to NetIRC2, so try that...
FeedPackage.Tags: IRC chat client network protocol
FeedPackage.Title: NetIrc2

FeedPackage.Description: The seventh version of the configuration-less, dynamic and self-adaptive database-first oriented Kerosene ORM library, with real full support for POCO objects, natural SQL-like syntax from plain C#, and advanced maps and lazy properties.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Streamlined architecture that provides enhanced control on the dependency properties, a 3x improvement in the performance of the core records mode, and a 4x improvement in the performance of the mapped records. Out of the box support for Sql Server, Oracle, Odbc and OleDb databases is also included.

FeedPackage.Tags: eCommerce Entity Framework Ketchup
FeedPackage.Title: Ketchup.Persistence.EntityFramework

FeedPackage.Description:
This component adds support for Carbonite to query and persists data entities via the Microsoft Entity Framework.
Carbonite includes a new lightweight ORM capable of mapping your objects and database by convention, configuration or code. Carbonite also conceals other popular ORMs into the same programming model so you will never need to deal again with hard-to-maintain heterogeneous data layers implementation models.
KEYSTONE is a modern, multi-paradigm, data-centric software development framework. Visit http://www.keystoneframework.com for more details.
